The paper deals with the verification of causal consistency in distributed implementations of data structures, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves formal verification and logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), and software engineering (cs.SE) as it discusses the complexity of verifying causal consistency and proposes solutions to circumvent the negative results.
